item.title: Family
item.media:title: Family
item.media:description:
New characters I kept for a long time, even though I've already introduced them from a drawing of them with Tokomo and Satiana. Also spoiler alert:

















































This family is actually Keiku's family.

Anyway, I shall explain their traits and backstories since I haven't done it yet.

Masako is Keiku, Ichiko, Hikari, and Ayame's mother and Keiichi's wife. She and her husband once lived in an exotic and wealthy town in Chrysolia; Masako is the rich girl while Keiichi is a commoner, and both loved each other. However, Masako's father disapproves of her relationship with Keiichi and tries to set her up an arranged marriage with a rich man. Masako dislikes it and would rather be with Keiichi. When Keiichi proposes to her, she happily accepts, much to the angry dismay of her father. On their wedding day, he kidnaps her back to their manor and locks her up in there. She thought she would never see her beloved again, but her sister, who approves of her and Keiichi's relationship, helps her escape and reunite with Keiichi. After they married, the couple moved away from their former home and into a simple town to start a family of their own. They had four daughters and loved them all so much. Everything is happy and perfect for them, at least until the Marcoribans show up. Masako is loving and caring to those close to her and loves her family. She is also friendly, but has a bit of a feisty streak.

Keiichi is Keiku, Ichiko, Hikari, and Ayame's father and Masako's husband. He and his wife once lived in an exotic and wealthy Town in Chrysolia; Keiichi is the commoner while Masako is the rich girl. He falls in love with her, but is afraid she wouldn't feel the same as two of them come from different classes. But when Masako confesses her love for him, he confessed the same for her. The two got engaged, but on the day of their wedding she went missing and Keiichi and his wedding guests started looking for his missing bride. As soon as he is ready to give up as he couldn't find her, Masako calls out to him and they reunite. After they married, they moved away from their former home and into a simple town to start a family of their own. They had four daughters and loved them all so much. Everything is happy and perfect for them, at least until the Marcoribans show up. Keiichi is a very decent fellow, loving and caring for his family, but has a bit of a pessimistic side, which his eldest daughter chastised him for.

Ichiko is the eldest daughter to Keiichi and Masako and eldest sister to Hikari, Ayame, and Keiku. She cares deeply about her sisters and parents and is friendly, but can be chastising, especially towards her father for his pessimism and Hikari for her recklessness and teasing of Ayame.

Hikari is the second oldest daughter to Keiichi and Masako and older sister to Ayame and Keiku and younger sister to Ichiko. She is a tomboy who loves playing sports and video games. She also likes to tease Ayame, much to Ichiko's dismay, but she loves all her sisters and parents.

Ayame is the younger daughter to Keiichi and Masako and younger sister to Ichiko and Hikari and older sister to Keiku. She is sweet but pretty sensitive. She is close to Keiku and Keiichi, but still loves her sisters and mother. She loves sweets like cupcakes, candies, and cookies. She also likes flowers and butterflies.

They all are going to appear in Adventures in Chrysolia.

The following characters are mine.
